Because California holds some of the most senior rights to the river, Arizona, Nevada and Mexico would experience cuts in deliveries before California, said Roger Patterson, assistant general manager of the Metropolitan Water District of Southern California.
I think a reasonably savvy person would have to say you "'re" going to see less water in that river," said Brad Udall, director of Western Water Assessment at the University of Colorado in Boulder, who was not a member of the report committee.
